theorem
Th36: (for x1,x2 being (Element of ( REAL n )) holds ((y1 in ( Line (x1,x2) ) & y2 in ( Line (x1,x2) )) implies (ex a st ( y2 - y1 ) = ( a * ( x2 - x1 ) ))))
proof
let x1 being (Element of ( REAL n )),x2 being (Element of ( REAL n ));
assume y1 in ( Line (x1,x2) );
then consider t such that A1: y1 = ( ( ( 1 - t ) * x1 ) + ( t * x2 ) );
assume y2 in ( Line (x1,x2) );
then consider s such that A2: y2 = ( ( ( 1 - s ) * x1 ) + ( s * x2 ) );
take ( s - t );
( y2 - y1 ) = ( ( ( ( ( 1 - s ) * x1 ) + ( s * x2 ) ) - ( ( 1 - t ) * x1 ) ) - ( t * x2 ) ) by A1,A2,RVSUM_1:39
.= ( ( ( ( s * x2 ) + ( ( 1 - s ) * x1 ) ) + ( - ( t * x2 ) ) ) + ( - ( ( 1 - t ) * x1 ) ) ) by RVSUM_1:15
.= ( ( ( ( s * x2 ) + ( - ( t * x2 ) ) ) + ( ( 1 - s ) * x1 ) ) + ( - ( ( 1 - t ) * x1 ) ) ) by RVSUM_1:15
.= ( ( ( ( s - t ) * x2 ) + ( ( 1 - s ) * x1 ) ) + ( - ( ( 1 - t ) * x1 ) ) ) by CKB12:1
.= ( ( ( s - t ) * x2 ) + ( ( ( 1 - s ) * x1 ) + ( - ( ( 1 - t ) * x1 ) ) ) ) by RVSUM_1:15
.= ( ( ( s - t ) * x2 ) + ( ( ( 1 - s ) - ( 1 - t ) ) * x1 ) ) by CKB12:1
.= ( ( ( s - t ) * x2 ) + ( ( - ( s - t ) ) * x1 ) )
.= ( ( s - t ) * ( x2 - x1 ) ) by CKB13:1;
hence thesis;
end;
